&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2x&lt;/b&gt; Glosses Skt. &lt;i&gt;āsādya&lt;/i&gt; 'near' (reading and identification by Klaus Wille with the help of a text reconstruction by Gudrun Melzer). If correctly read, the gloss does not translate &lt;i&gt;āsādya&lt;/i&gt; in its grammaticalised sense of 'near, close by', but in a more literal sense 'having approached, obtained'. The reading of the first two akṣaras is made difficult by a piece of paper from another fragment that sticks on the surface (i.e. the text itself is probably not abraded). A large part of the second consonantal element of the second akṣara can be seen, which seems compatible with &lt;i&gt;m&lt;/i&gt;, although this &lt;i&gt;m&lt;/i&gt; must then have been a little different from that of the following akṣara. The akṣara &lt;i&gt;rmeṃ&lt;/i&gt; is lowered compared to the preceding akṣaras, in order to remain under the lower part of the akṣara &lt;i&gt;dya&lt;/i&gt; of the Skt. text.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
